The paper discusses a deep learning approach to a brain lesion object-detection task, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also focuses on modelling individual rater behaviour and multirater consensus, which involves machine learning techniques such as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of human raters in distinguishing between similar classes, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
